[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying constructor access**\n\nI'm thinking about whether a non-public class allows access to its public constructors. I wonder if getConstructor can still find public members even if the class itself isn't public. Actually, it seems that getConstructor does return public constructors, as long as the constructor is public. But then I consider serialization as a separate issue. Should I be using a public class? Plus, does serialization impact non-serializable aspects within a parent/prototype context?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e6ec8c9a958b8900169fa45c78fa0819fa7d412cb9d076e3d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-kXZz8My0IEiImu3G-mu34CTgJgpWy9mbcucUSSFIo1rgtQVdg3iUnjnBxAwzfya8CkMYYkcd4K-OGTOnL9HaFe0esi1LN4OCs9b_ibHswGpikMDHsik_Yw7FxVq95K6sfyda4QB8ryT2KZFGhUqt8Wz395-QCk1imOceASsjv6j_xsC4X0xFDNqSbWJmE-WOLosYuuMj6LJkJMCoQra4JB5rG9kzHC2IFtEI-xt5uNmbFR2UAELFQx4HjfQB5c3TDzO6_JT_M8Bn3m3SoDq1DKkaJAPhtokjQ2L6XVvWXFi9pzdLPfVgbQG34RqvYEDd_YvKQgTSCG7Z91lvAU1_-X9dH6MJMbNHjY82XW-MsZBskLzmSoRWSZA33Rt8f3ZlwgoQQ-supmVxpkcFHZNAFYE-RTwFGsvyz9XyfjWWjAelnmG2YAWoGwyKdh89OVL_T3F_8QYDhp7I1YroHhVnQ6unan7M5Xj3pwqsMrOm7vhHnpZwWwwUnF6e9AdijdFb8Y_xMJ9PGDIkC93omNsTUcKIRT5GyPJwBJaAVdvWoruWVvzklDQmhaxaq3whLPiPw3buFR4FylycHU4p1Gc--Doky4zJa1-HAEXWh2eJGTVaKDRmsX5mgkdbpi5lTzMY-fvCpN1Xr70gAfDTtdFwwP4EtafTvZ5Mky-Wj2eblBNyAE3eCN0J6-sBo0qAAExktD8LCTQt0QrXcvHIL14Teqw-VWmpfv5Uw5SyUO72vQnVwI-sgm8FIMrN4ppNM_ViPuHqIy6sQuneSrTa05x052vLdXoOE0adNmJzlua5kUu5KNdNiUOJ2tIPB6ZNv_2qPeg1hVXahM-pjE3Iv-yMvgkXLoOalrJRZ2CI3-T0G8o9oqeultkAUJHwNeGqP9_KbsiQZT2zOWya0mCgwRHHpvCK-qcu02jdJT3fC00B9TtrJK9qy5B1_83QBQSMgwxelmiVEpmmOwfLVbk4ELCkBKUEfKn7obwh7XFsInH5jG1fxDyXwsKyD7ZozpvjY7fNMvvIskOI-VQ3g7F4hvEZCp7LyQWoQt2qP9kIs0xgsqCFqucyBU4zZ-GRol97rxZmVrBiQHKGFJL-mwFYcYVS6SKsIzrDEmkebK4Cc-nL8vFvQqpLQQ-QvpFcKbqCfgIwljZZJtwAvxBjHE4hkFYZrbMUi_v33HO-Le1ks6YdnpSNPBsknSuIS9xIgm78pRJHJToEAQ2RGHCQmFrnFRP